ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Right before I do a tic, I feel like my insides are itchy.
Notes: 0 = not at all true ; 1 = little true ; 2 = pretty much true ; 3 = very much true

ElementDescription: Right before I do a tic, I feel pressure inside my brain or body.
Notes: 0 = not at all true ; 1 = little true ; 2 = pretty much true ; 3 = very much true

ElementDescription: Right before I do a tic, I feel "wound up" or tense inside
Notes: 0 = not at all true ; 1 = little true ; 2 = pretty much true ; 3 = very much true

ElementDescription: Right before I do a tic, I feel like something is not "just right."
Notes: 0 = not at all true ; 1 = little true ; 2 = pretty much true ; 3 = very much true

ElementDescription: Right before I do a tic, I feel like something isn't complete.
Notes: 0 = not at all true ; 1 = little true ; 2 = pretty much true ; 3 = very much true

ElementDescription: Right before I do a tic, I feel like there is energy in my body that needs to get out.
Notes: 0 = not at all true ; 1 = little true ; 2 = pretty much true ; 3 = very much true

ElementDescription: I have these feelings almost all the time before I do a tic.
Notes: 0 = not at all true ; 1 = little true ; 2 = pretty much true ; 3 = very much true

ElementDescription: These feelings happen for every tic I have.
Notes: 0 = not at all true ; 1 = little true ; 2 = pretty much true ; 3 = very much true

ElementDescription: After I do the tic, the itchiness, energy, pressure, tense feelings, or feelings that something isn't "just right" or complete go away, at least for a little while.
Notes: 0 = not at all true ; 1 = little true ; 2 = pretty much true ; 3 = very much true

ElementDescription: I am able to stop my tics, even if only for a short period of time.
Notes: 0 = not at all true ; 1 = little true ; 2 = pretty much true ; 3 = very much true

ElementDescription: PUTS Total: Sum all items used (see version_form data for 9-item or 10-item scale)
